FBIS3-48961 "dreeu001_p_94010" FBIS-EEU-94-001 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Jan 1994 POLAND Striking Miners Reach Agreement With Government LD3112084393 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 0100 GMT 31 Dec 93 LD3112084393 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network Language: Polish Article Type:BFN [Text] Representatives of the striking workforce of the barite colliery in Boguszow have reached an agreement with the government that makes it possible for the strike to be suspended or broken off. The state budget will give 12 billion zlotys to the Fund for the Walbrzych Area so that the mine can operate for three more months.
